## 2) Responder Desktop App (Rust / Tauri & React)

### Working Condition
The React frontend is well-built with a clean component structure, dedicated hooks, services, and utility layers. The Tauri/Rust backend now includes auto-assembly logic for the fragmented model file (added in prior fix session).

### Errors & Problems

#### 🚨 CRITICAL: Missing `llama-server.exe` executable
- **File:** `src-tauri/src/main.rs` (line 17)
- **Problem:** The Rust setup function attempts to spawn `binaries/llama-server.exe` but this file does not exist in the repository. The app will print an error and **skip all AI sidecar initialization**, meaning the local Gemma model will never run.
- **Impact:** The offline AI capability (Rule 5: Offline Resilience) is completely non-functional.

#### 🚨 CRITICAL: Hardcoded Cloud Run URLs in React frontend
- **File:** `src/config.js` (lines 1-2)
  - `BACKEND_URL` → `https://warden-backend-774533752332.us-central1.run.app`
  - `SIMULATION_URL` → `https://warden-simulation-774533752332.us-central1.run.app`
- **File:** `src/api.js` (line 1)
  - `BASE` → `https://warden-backend-774533752332.us-central1.run.app`
- **Problem:** Two separate files hardcode Cloud Run URLs. The app will fail to communicate with any local backend. Violates Rules.md Rule 3.
- **Impact:** All REST API calls (fetching alerts, updating status, fetching reports) and WebSocket connections will fail when running locally.

#### ⚠️ MEDIUM: Unused Tauri plugin imports
- **File:** `src-tauri/src/main.rs` (lines 4-5)
- **Problem:** `tauri_plugin_shell::ShellExt` and `tauri_plugin_shell::process::CommandEvent` are imported but never used (the spawn logic uses `std::process::Command` directly).

